# Module architecture

Follow [ARCHITECTURE.md](../../ARCHITECTURE.md) §2–§3 and §12. Dependencies flow **downward only**:

```
commons  ←  client
commons  ←  server
(client used in server tests only, not production)
```

## commons — protocol kernel

- `Message`, `Command`, `Header`, `Headers`, `MessageBuffer`, `TransportType`.
- **No** dependency on `client` or `server`.
- Wire encode/decode only — no transport or session logic.

## client — STOMP client

| Layer | Packages | Role |
|-------|----------|------|
| Public API | `dev.vepo.stomp4j.client` | `StompClient`, `Subscription`, `UserCredential` |
| Protocol | `client.protocol`, `client.protocol.v1_*` | Version-specific STOMP commands |
| Transport SPI | `client.transport`, `client.internal.transport` | TCP/WebSocket I/O |
| Internal | `client.internal` | `StompClientImpl` — connection lifecycle |

- **Exports** only public packages (see `module-info.java`).
- **SPI:** `TransportProvider`, `Stomp` — register in `provides` + `META-INF/services`.

## server — embeddable STOMP server

| Layer | Packages | Role |
|-------|----------|------|
| Public API | `dev.vepo.stomp4j.server`, `server.auth` | `StompServer`, handlers, authenticator |
| Channels | `server.channels` (internal) | TCP NIO, WebSocket (Vert.x) |
| Session | `server.session` (internal) | Per-connection state machine |

- Handlers (`MessageHandler`, `SubscriptionHandler`) are the application boundary.
- Channel/session details stay internal.

## When adding a feature

1. Decide module: protocol change → `commons`; client-only → `client`; server-only → `server`.
2. Update `module-info.java` if exports or SPI change.
3. Add tests in the same module.
4. Update ARCHITECTURE.md §3 / §13.

## Violations

```java
// ❌ commons importing client
import dev.vepo.stomp4j.client.StompClient;

// ❌ server production code depending on client
// (test scope only is fine)

// ✅ server uses commons Message
import dev.vepo.stomp4j.commons.protocol.Message;
```
